OL,3,CGeneral Election 2024: A look at the
OL,4,Cancient city battling modern problems
OL,6,FA couple of miles across town,
OL,7,FGloucester's docks shimmer in the
OL,8,Fsunlight, the beneficiaries of twenty
OL,9,Fyears of regeneration and now a major
OL,10,Fshopping and leisure destination. But
OL,11,Fnot everyone has money to spend.
OL,13,FNine of the city's neighbourhoods are
OL,14,Fin the top 10% most deprived in the UK.
OL,16,FMore than 4,000 households are on the
OL,17,Fwaiting list for the city's social
OL,18,Fhousing, and violent crime in the
OL,19,Fpoorest neighbourhood - Barton and
OL,20,FTredworth - is three times the
OL,21,Fnational average.
